Detailed Description

Functor to print skip/back information when a static data block is entered.

Skip/back information can be enabled/disabled across the entire unparser by calling the set_skipback_reporting() method. This callback can be removed per object type without confusing other objects that define a similar callbacks (for example, to disable skip/back reporting for static data blocks but leave it in place for instructions).
